  "prompt": "I am interested in a girl but she wants to just be friends. What do I do?",
  "response": "Navigating feelings for someone who prefers to remain friends can be challenging, but there are positive ways to handle the situation:\n\n1. **Respect Her Decision**: It's important to respect her feelings and the boundaries she has set. If she wants to be friends, it's key to accept that and not pressure her.\n\n2. **Focus on Friendship**: Embrace the opportunity to build a strong friendship. This can be rewarding in its own right, and it may also provide insight into her feelings over time.\n\n3. **Give It Time**: Feelings can change. By being patient and allowing your friendship to grow, it's possible that she may come to see you in a different light.\n\n4. **Manage Your Feelings**: It might be helpful to process your own feelings. Talking to friends or journaling can help you sort through your emotions while you navigate this friendship.\n\n5. **Think About Your Needs**: Consider what you want from this relationship. If you're finding it hard to remain just friends, it may be best to create some distance for your own emotional well-being.\n\n6. **Be Open and Honest**: If you feel comfortable, you can express your feelings in a straightforward manner, ensuring that you communicate your respect for her stance. Just be prepared for any response she might have.\n\n7. **Keep Exploring**: Don't put your life on hold. Stay open to meeting new people and exploring other romantic interests while being friends with her.\n\nUltimately, it\u2019s about striking a balance between your feelings and respecting her wishes.",
